    <a title="Jade" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1514817-jade"><img alt="Jade" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1363347763p2/1514817.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3982499539?book_show_action=true">Jun 06, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jade" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jade" href="/user/show/1514817-jade">Jade</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/46010953-a-voyage-for-madmen">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1514817-jade?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3982499539" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2268765989572394266">The end of this book leaves you both in awe and sadness. The wonder of the drive (and stubborn stupidity) which saw these solo sailors attempt to be the first or fastest man to circumnavigate the globe. The reality of how being truly alone physically and mentally for a long period of time can make or break you. <br/><br/>It was also very interesting to learn about why sailors feel the passion for all things nautical. Coming from Plymouth myself and having previously worked at a yacht club I’ve frequently </span>
  <span id="freeText2268765989572394266" style="display:none">The end of this book leaves you both in awe and sadness. The wonder of the drive (and stubborn stupidity) which saw these solo sailors attempt to be the first or fastest man to circumnavigate the globe. The reality of how being truly alone physically and mentally for a long period of time can make or break you. <br /><br />It was also very interesting to learn about why sailors feel the passion for all things nautical. Coming from Plymouth myself and having previously worked at a yacht club I’ve frequently been around people who sail, and as much as I love the sea, I’ve always preferred the beach side of things! I can’t say this book has changed my feelings, but I have a new found respect for the craft.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2268765989572394266" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


