<span id="freeTextContainer10948572517575511343">I read this book just in time for the 50th anniversary of the Golden Globe Race and I am glad I did. The book is about the trials and joys of the sailors who attempted to sail around the world nonstop in 1968. After reading this book, I am confused why anyone would try again, considering everything these sailors went through. This was well researched and kept me up way too late reading. A good book makes you feel sad when you are finished. A great book leaves you with I want more. This was a gre</span>
  <span id="freeText10948572517575511343" style="display:none">I read this book just in time for the 50th anniversary of the Golden Globe Race and I am glad I did. The book is about the trials and joys of the sailors who attempted to sail around the world nonstop in 1968. After reading this book, I am confused why anyone would try again, considering everything these sailors went through. This was well researched and kept me up way too late reading. A good book makes you feel sad when you are finished. A great book leaves you with I want more. This was a great book. If you love adventure and endurance tales, this book should be at the top of your list.</span>
