        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4122061272" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17881455730404617076">Nichols&apos; <i>A Voyage for Madmen</i> chronicles a 1968 journey around the world by boat. Nine men depart from England but only one succeeds. Putting aside the general adventure of a race like this one, I was particularly intrigued by the motivations of these men. For the most part, they have nothing more than an uncontrollable impulse to <i>go</i>. But once they start sailing down the Atlantic, the reality of their decision--the danger and the loneliness--hits each sailor differently. They are left with themse</span>
  <span id="freeText17881455730404617076" style="display:none">Nichols' <i>A Voyage for Madmen</i> chronicles a 1968 journey around the world by boat. Nine men depart from England but only one succeeds. Putting aside the general adventure of a race like this one, I was particularly intrigued by the motivations of these men. For the most part, they have nothing more than an uncontrollable impulse to <i>go</i>. But once they start sailing down the Atlantic, the reality of their decision--the danger and the loneliness--hits each sailor differently. They are left with themselves. I worry that this is how we make many decisions. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17881455730404617076" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
